  "body": "<!-- This form is for bug reports and feature requests ONLY! \r\n\r\nIf you're looking for help check [Stack Overflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/kubernetes) and the [troubleshooting guide](https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/debug-application-cluster/troubleshooting/).\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**: bug\r\n\r\n/kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**: When a GCE instance running COS restarts, all installed Flexvolume drivers disappear.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**: Drivers should not disappear.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**: Start a cluster on GCE with `cluster/kube-up.sh`. Install a Flexvolume driver on one of the nodes and then restart that node.\r\n\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**: The default volume plugin directory of `/etc/srv/...` is an overlayfs over a location in `/tmp`.\r\n",
